§lWelcome to Realistic Unreality!§r

This is a Kitchen Sink-esque style modpack, with an emphasis on realism without the realism.

§lThe Lore:§r

You spent all night trying to put together a crappy modpack to no avail. Right as your patience is dwindling, you find a mod on 4chan that's supposed to fix an error. You add it, and try to load the modpack. Since it takes forever to load, you end up taking a nap...

When you awake, your house is gone. You're lying on gravel. The world around you is definitely still Earth, but much smaller, and a lot more cubic.

You come to the conclusion that Earth is now in Minecraft, and you are too. You're no stranger to the game, so you know the drill.

§lThe Credits:§r

This modpack was made for the OneShot Discord. You may still use this modpack for your own purposes.

Official downloads are on GitHub:
https://github.com/wistlyr/Realistic-Unreality

For support, please see the #realisticunreality channel on our Discord:
https://discord.gg/oneshot

§1Don't have enough crystals? Try this to double your certus quartz and your fluix crystals!§r Smashing a crystal into powder and mixing it with sand will create a seed. Leave this in water for a long time and it will eventually turn into a pure crystal! §1Now that you have pure crystals, it's time to make the Controller! This is the central block of an AE system and it will replace your Energy Acceptor as the way to power the network.§a While a network without a Controller can only have 8 devices, §1the Controller allows you to have more than that. §rSimply, each device on a network requires 1 channel. The Controller provides §132 channels per side§r, although the basic ME Cable can only carry 8 channels. Make more controllers if you need them - but be sure §1all your controllers are touching each other§r, or else it won't work.

§6Tired of waiting around for your crystals to grow§r§6?§r §r§r§r§r
§r§6§r§rCrystal Growth Accelerators can make certus seeds and fluix seeds grow into pure crystals much faster!§r They do consume a lot of power, so consider disabling them when you are not using them.§a A Toggle Bus will disable a part of your network when a redstone signal is applied to it.

Welcome to Environmental Tech!

This mod features large multiblock machines, like the Solar Controller and the Void Ore Miner.

The multiblocks can be automatically assembled, if you right click with the Assembler on the Controller block that you wish to build the structure for. It'll tell you the materials you need. Once the materials are all in your inventory, right click the Controller with the Assembler again, and it'll build your structure!

In order to progress through the mod, you'll need tons of Litherite to start off with. Use that to build your first Void Ore Miner (Tier 1) - which will mine Litherite, and the next tier crystal, for you. Build the next tier Ore Miner with your newly acquired crystals, and repeat the cycle until you reach Tier 6.

All of the crystals are used in lategame recipes.

The higher the tier of the Ore Miner, the faster it runs. Certain ores can only be obtained from the highest tiers of Ore Miner - JEI shows which ores are obtainable, and the chances to get them.

The Dimension Enscriber enables you to construct dimensions, using an Empty Dimension Tab and Dimlets.

Place a Realized Dimension Tab in the Dimension Builder to build the dimension.

It will need massive amounts of power - You may need to power the Dimension Builder from multiple sides.
The Dimension Editor lets you insert some items and dimlets into existing dimensions.

The Dimlet Workbench lets you disassemble dimlets, and craft your own custom ones.

Every dimlet is made out of six parts:

A base

A Control Circuit of the same rarity as the dimlet (from 0 to 6).

An Energy Module. There are three types: basic, regular, and advanced corresponding with the different rarities (0,1 for basic, 2,3 for regular and 4,5,6 for advanced).

A Memory Module with the same three levels.

A Type Controller part. For every type of dimlet (biome, mob, material, ...) there is a corresponding part.

A specific essence block or item.
The Phased Field Generator will let you survive §4(barely)§r in an unpowered RFTools dimension, at the cost of large amounts of power.
Dimlet Parcels contain dimlet parts. They drop rarely from Endermen.
The Enchantment Extractor can pull enchants off items and onto books. It can also split Enchanted Books with multiple enchants.
The Sludge Refiner processes Sludge into blocks like Clay, Sand and Gravel.

Black Hole Storage works a lot like Deep Storage Units from MineFactory Reloaded. They're able to store insane amounts of any one item. The Controller acts very much like the Controller from Storage Drawers.
The Animal Baby Seperator can seperate baby animals from adult animals. It's useful for making an automatic animal farm.
The Plant Fertilizer automatically fertilizes crops when supplied with power and fertilizer.
The Resources Fisher automatically fishes when placed over a 3x3 pool of water, and supplied with power.

The Protein Reactor generates Protein from animal products. 

The Protein can be used to generate power in the Protein Generator.
